From ca97aeaca9f2a8b5688aded930ffe7eb3ba4ba4c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Pankaj Bharadiya <pankaj.laxminarayan.bharadiya@intel.com>
Date: Thu, 20 Feb 2020 22:25:00 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 4266/4530] drm/i915/display/cdclk: Make WARN* drm specific
 where drm_priv ptr is available

drm specific WARN* calls include device information in the
backtrace, so we know what device the warnings originate from.

Covert all the calls of WARN* with device specific drm_WARN*
variants in functions where drm_i915_private struct pointer is
readily available.

The conversion was done automatically with below coccinelle semantic
patch. checkpatch errors/warnings are fixed manually.

@rule1@
identifier func, T;
@@
func(...) {
...
struct drm_i915_private *T = ...;
<+...
(
-WARN(
+drm_WARN(&T->drm,
...)
|
-WARN_ON(
+drm_WARN_ON(&T->drm,
...)
|
-WARN_ONCE(
+drm_WARN_ONCE(&T->drm,
...)
|
-WARN_ON_ONCE(
+drm_WARN_ON_ONCE(&T->drm,
...)
)
...+>
}

@rule2@
identifier func, T;
@@
func(struct drm_i915_private *T,...) {
<+...
(
-WARN(
+drm_WARN(&T->drm,
...)
|
-WARN_ON(
+drm_WARN_ON(&T->drm,
...)
|
-WARN_ONCE(
+drm_WARN_ONCE(&T->drm,
...)
|
-WARN_ON_ONCE(
+drm_WARN_ON_ONCE(&T->drm,
...)
)
...+>
}

Signed-off-by: Pankaj Bharadiya <pankaj.laxminarayan.bharadiya@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Jani Nikula <jani.nikula@intel.com>
Link: https://patchwork.freedesktop.org/patch/msgid/20200220165507.16823-2-pankaj.laxminarayan.bharadiya@intel.com
